                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>Montreal</placeName>\n                <date>18 March 1850</date>\n            </p>\n            <p>My Dear Sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I have to acknowledge the receipt of<lb/> your long letter of the\n                        <date>20<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi></date> with the Occidents</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">My a/ct Curr<add>?</add>stowed Balance due you of 1. 11. 5</p>\n            <table cols=\"3\" rows=\"5\">\n                <row>\n                    <cell><persName>Moss</persName> &amp; <persName>Levy's</persName> Subscriptions\n                        were</cell>\n                    <cell>2. 2. 6</cell>\n                    <cell/>\n                </row>\n                <row>\n                    <cell>2 expresses 1/11. 1/11—Remittance of</cell>\n                    <cell>\n                        <hi rend=\"underline\">1. 13. 10</hi>\n                    </cell>\n                    <cell>0. 8 .8</cell>\n                </row>\n                <row>\n                    <cell><persName>Alt Davids</persName> Subscriptions <add>?</add> 16.45 &amp; 16\n                        49—</cell>\n                    <cell>3<add>?</add>/</cell>\n                    <cell/>\n                </row>\n                <row>\n                    <cell>do——to Publication Society——</cell>\n                    <cell>5/35/</cell>\n                    <cell/>\n                </row>\n                <row>\n                    <cell>less Express <date>9 March</date></cell>\n                    <cell>\n                        <hi rend=\"underline\">2/6</hi>\n                    </cell>\n                    <cell>\n                        <hi rend=\"underline\">1. 12. 6</hi>\n                    </cell>\n                </row>\n            </table>\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\">3. 12. 7</p>\n            <p>This Amount I will enclose <persName>Mr Benjamin's</persName> a/ct <add>?</add>\n                but<lb/> I frequently send for it. There are some subscriptions that I do<lb/> not\n                ask for as the parties would probably withdraw their<lb/>\n                <add>?</add>—but as they are certain to pay all they owe, I<lb/> think it advisable\n                to let their dues accumulate—such<lb/> as <persName>H Solomon</persName>,\n                    <persName>A E Hart</persName>. It is uncertain what<lb/> number will continue\n                their subscriptions for the coming<lb/> year—there may be 10 or 11. If you print an\n                extra<lb/> quantity of <date>April</date> numbers and you send me a couple<lb/> of\n                Dozen copies, I will have one sent to every Israelite<lb/> in the province who is\n                able to subscribe and thus<lb/> ascertain if they have become more disposed than\n                formerly<lb/> to support the publication. Some are subscribers to the<lb/> Asmonean\n                which pleases them for its being more of a News<lb/>paper and the <add>?</add> of\n                our people wish more to know<lb/> what</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3xw48g7t/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
